>> tentative agenda is to frame a practical process for developing a CUUC
>> vision statement for possible congregational vote in late autumn.*
>>
>> Before that meeting, Patricia wisely advised that I should check a few
>> assumptions with you so that we are aligned with your expectations.
>>
>> My current working assumptions are:
>>
>> - you are expecting and/or would encourage COM to move the ball on
>> revising our vision statement.
>> - The process should be democratic and participatory, but structured
>> enough to avoid large-scale open-ended drafting.
>> - A likely model would be:
>>   - gather and organize existing source material
>>   - possibly do one additional focused input step with the congregation
>>   - have a small group synthesize themes and draft a few candidate
>> statements
>>   - bring those back to the congregation for structured feedback and
>> discernment
>>   - revise and bring a final version for vote (SPARC is having a vote in
>> late Autumn I think)?
>> - Existing materials such as the Mission Statement, Covenant, UU
>> values/principles, and the SPARC findings (and anything else you may
>> suggest?) should/could be treated as meaningful source material rather t=
han
>> starting from a blank page.
>> - It may be useful to leave open the possibility of using a workshop
>> format later, including materials already gathered, if that seems helpfu=
l
>> in moving from themes to draft options.
>> - summer would likely be slow so the majority of effort will be in the
>> next couple of months and then re-engaging in September
>>
>>
>> The main things I would be grateful for your guidance on are:
>>
>> 1. Does piggybacking on the SPARC vote (and possibly their survey
>> findings) make sense?
>> 2. Does the small-group synthesis / broad-congregational-feedback model
>> sound appropriate to you?
>> 3. Are there any governance/leadership checkpoints you would want built
>> into the process?
>> 4. Are there particular groups or documents we should be sure to include=
?
>>
>> I=E2=80=99m not seeking polished answers :) This is more of a sanity che=
ck to
>> help ensure that Tuesday=E2=80=99s discussion starts from the right assu=
mptions.
>>
>> Thanks for your time,
>> Alex
>>
>>
